The paper focuses on developing a saliency model based on deep features of convolutional neural networks for predicting human fixations. This involves the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and machine learning algorithms (cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE) to analyze and interpret visual data. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed model using various metrics, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
